# Common build context exclusions for the three Python Dockerfiles that
# share the project root (Dockerfile + Dockerfile.card-worker). The
# frontend and java-api have their own contexts + their own ignore files.
#
# Anything listed here never enters `docker build`, so the resulting
# image stays small and dev-only artefacts (mlruns/, tests, .git) can't
# leak into a production layer.

# --- Local IDE / OS noise ---
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
.idea/
.vscode/
*.iml

# --- VCS + virtualenvs + caches ---
.git/
.gitignore
.venv/
venv/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
celerybeat-schedule

# --- Other services' build contexts ---
frontend/
java-api/

# --- ML / data artefacts ---
mlruns/
data/
reports/

# --- Test code (the image runs the prod entrypoint; tests run in CI) ---
tests/

# --- Documentation + recon output ---
docs/
deploy-recon/

# --- Docs in the root (keep README.md) ---
*.md
!README.md

# --- Deploy infra (k8s reads secrets/keys at runtime, not from the image) ---
# Keep deploy/jwt-keys/ available for local dev convenience — once helm
# takes over, this whole directory should be excluded.
deploy/charts/
deploy/terraform/
deploy/monitoring/
deploy/nginx/
deploy/postgres-init/
deploy/scripts/

# --- This recon output ---
deploy-recon/

# --- Env files (compose injects them at runtime via env_file:) ---
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
